## Plan: Fix off-by-one error in `processItems`

**Root cause:** `src/utils.ts`, line 7 — the loop condition `i < items.length - 1` stops one iteration early, so the last array element is never processed.

**The fix — one line change:**
```typescript
// Before (buggy)
for (let i = 0; i < items.length - 1; i++) {

// After (fixed)
for (let i = 0; i < items.length; i++) {
```

**Why it's broken:** For an array of length N, valid indices are `0` through `N-1`. The condition `i < items.length - 1` means the loop only reaches index `N-2`, permanently skipping the last element.

**Verification:** Run `npm test` (uses Vitest). The existing test suite in `tests/utils.test.ts` already has 4 `processItems` tests — covering empty, single-item, two-item, and three-item arrays — that will all pass after the fix. No new tests are needed.
